// =========================================================================
// FIX Round151: DEBUG OUTPUT GATING STATUS
// =========================================================================
// Most std::cerr outputs in this file are gated with debug_level checks:
//   - debug_level >= 1: Constructor, boundary conditions, grid params, config
//   - debug_level >= 2: Hot-path diagnostics, halo validation, CFL details
//   - debug_level >= 3: Heavy diagnostics (full tensor min/max/zeros/nonzero scans)
//   - CRITICAL/ERROR: Always output (appropriate for fatal conditions)
//   - WARNING: Gated with debug_level >= 1 for non-fatal issues
//
// EXCEPTION (intentionally ungated):
//   - CRITICAL ERROR messages for fatal validation failures
//   - Device mismatch warnings (first occurrence only via throttle)
//   - rdnw/dnw/rdn/dn validation warnings (first occurrence only)
//
// PERFORMANCE NOTE: flush() calls are inside debug blocks after Round150.
// FIX Round154 POLICY: Heavy tensor scans (min/max on large arrays) should
// use debug_level >= 3 or sampling-based approach if added in the future.
// Current level 2 gating is acceptable as it prevents production overhead.
// =========================================================================
//
// =========================================================================
// SIGN CONVENTION DOCUMENTATION (WRF-COMPLIANT REFACTOR 2025-12-25)
// =========================================================================
// This code follows WRF STANDARD sign convention for vertical metrics:
//
// WRF STANDARD (ALL POSITIVE):
//   - dnw  = eta(k+1) - eta(k) > 0  (positive layer thickness in eta coords)
//   - rdnw = 1/dnw > 0              (positive reciprocal)
//   - dn   = 0.5*(dnw(k) + dnw(k-1)) > 0  (mass-level spacing)
//   - rdn  = 1/dn > 0               (positive reciprocal)
//   - rdzw = rdnw > 0               (same as rdnw, used in vertical ops)
//
// CODE INTERNAL (matches WRF):
//   - rdnw_ > 0  (stored as positive, matching WRF)
//   - rdn_  > 0  (stored as positive, matching WRF)
//   - dnw_  > 0  (positive, derived from rdnw_)
//   - rdzw  = rdnw > 0  (direct use, no negation needed)
//
// STORAGE:
//   - rdnw input: rdnw_[k] = |rdnw[k]|  (ensure positive)
//   - rdn input:  rdn_[k] = |rdn[k]|    (ensure positive)
//   - GridDnw fallback: rdnw = 1/|dnw|  (positive)
//   - GridDn fallback:  rdn = 1/|dn|    (positive)
//
// USAGE:
//   - rdzw = rdnw (direct, no negation)
//   - dnw = 1/rdnw (direct, positive result)
//   - All vertical derivatives use positive rdnw/rdn directly
// =========================================================================
//
// =========================================================================
// OPT Pass34: from_blob + const_cast CLASSIFICATION
// =========================================================================
// torch::from_blob() requires non-const pointer. Many inputs from Fortran
// are const float*. This section classifies the const_cast usage patterns:
//
// READ-ONLY INPUTS (Fortran owns, C++ views, never writes back):
//   - Terrain slopes: sin_alpha_x, sin_alpha_y, cos_alpha_x, cos_alpha_y
//   - Base states: p_base, mu_base, ph_base, th_base
//   - Grid metrics: rdn, rdnw, fnm, fnp, c1f, c2f, c1h, c2h
//   - Diffusion: Kh_mom, Kv_mom, Kh_scalar, Kv_scalar
//   - External BC: u_ext, v_ext, w_ext, t_ext, ph_ext, mu_ext
//   - Projection: f, e, sina, cosa
//   CONTRACT: These tensors are used read-only. If AD requires gradients,
//             they should be .clone()'d after from_blob.
//
// CLONED ON CREATE (safe - data copied immediately):
//   - c1f_, c2f_, c1h_, c2h_ (use .clone() after from_blob)
//   - f_, e_, sina_, cosa_ (use .clone() after from_blob)
//   CONTRACT: Safe for any use. Clone breaks aliasing with Fortran memory.
//
// READ-WRITE OUTPUTS (Fortran allocates, C++ computes, writes back):
//   - Tendency arrays: ru_tend, rv_tend, rw_tend, ph_tend, t_tend, mu_tend
//   - State variables: u, v, w, t, ph, mu (when used as output buffers)
//   CONTRACT: Caller expects modified data after return. No clone needed.
//
// VALIDATION: All from_blob sites have LINT_EXCEPTION comments indicating
// they have been reviewed for const-correctness safety.
// =========================================================================

